# Command terragrunt

## What does this command do:

the command that applies a DRY infrastructure automation orchestration system

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: curl -sSfL https://github.com/gruntwork-io/terragrunt/releases/download/v1.0.3/terragrunt_linux_amd64 -o ~/.local/bin/terragrunt && chmod +x ~/.local/bin/terragrunt
For Raspberry Pi install using: curl -sSfL https://github.com/gruntwork-io/terragrunt/releases/download/v1.0.3/terragrunt_linux_arm64 -o ~/.local/bin/terragrunt && chmod +x ~/.local/bin/terragrunt
For Mac install using: brew install terragrunt

## Command path

For Fedora run: ~/.local/bin/terragrunt
For Raspberry Pi run: ~/.local/bin/terragrunt
For Mac run: /opt/homebrew/bin/terragrunt

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://docs.terragrunt.com/

## Command options

# OpenTofu/Terraform wrappers (pass-through to tofu/terraform)
terragrunt init                          # prepare working directory
terragrunt plan                          # show changes
terragrunt apply                         # create/update infrastructure
terragrunt destroy                       # destroy infrastructure
terragrunt output                        # show output values
terragrunt validate                      # check configuration is valid
terragrunt state <subcommand>            # advanced state management
terragrunt show                          # show current state or saved plan

# Multi-module stack commands
terragrunt run-all plan                  # plan all modules in dependency order
terragrunt run-all apply                 # apply all modules in dependency order
terragrunt run-all destroy               # destroy all modules in reverse order

# Stack commands
terragrunt stack <subcommand>            # manage Terragrunt stacks

# Discovery
terragrunt find                          # find relevant Terragrunt configs
terragrunt list                          # list relevant Terragrunt configs

# Configuration inspection
terragrunt render                        # print fully-resolved terragrunt.hcl
terragrunt dag                           # show dependency graph (DAG)
terragrunt hcl <subcommand>              # interact with HCL files
terragrunt info                          # show Terragrunt settings

# Backend
terragrunt backend <subcommand>          # interact with backend infrastructure

# Catalog / scaffolding
terragrunt catalog                       # browse module catalog UI
terragrunt scaffold                      # scaffold a new module

# Arbitrary command execution
terragrunt exec -- <cmd> [args]          # run any command inside Terragrunt's wrapper

# Global flags
--log-level error|warn|info|debug|trace  # set log verbosity (default: info)
--no-color                               # disable ANSI colour output
--non-interactive                        # skip all prompts (useful in CI)
--working-dir <path>                     # override working directory
--strict-mode                            # treat deprecated features as errors
--experiment-mode                        # enable all experiments
